<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Expressing postion of 'radial-gradient' with the CSS3 notation</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css3-images/#gradients" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="'background-position' of a 'radial-gradient' expressed in the CSS3 notation is supported." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #test
            {
                background: radial-gradient(right 10px bottom 7px, ellipse, yellow, white, black);
                height: 500px;
                margin: 10px;
                width: 500px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is quarter circle which starts as yellow at the bottom left and gradually changes to white and then extends to a black.</p>
        <div id="test"></div>
    </body>
</html>
